AS INTRODUCED
6
7
An Act relating to child welfare; creating the Child
7
Welfare Task Force; specifying duties; requiring
8
submission of certain report; stipulating membership;
8
providing for selection of chair and creation of
9
committees; specifying requirements for meetings and
9
quorum; prohibiting certain compensation; providing
10
for staffing and information sharing; providing for
10
codification; and providing an effective date.
11
11
12
12
13
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13
14
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14
15
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-10-104 of Title 10A, unless
15
16
there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16
17
A. There is hereby created, until November 1, 2027, the Child
17
18
Welfare Task Force. The task force shall study, evaluate, and make
18
19
recommendations regarding policies, programs, and proposed
19
20
legislation that will:
20
21
1. Further reduce the time to permanency in the foster care
21
22
system;
22
23
2. Further reduce the amount of reentries to foster care after
23
24
discharge to permanency;
24
Req. No. 2882 Page 1

1
3. Identify risk factors that lead to the removal of children
1
2
from their biological parents’ home; and
2
3
4. Identify and propose areas of support for biological
3
4
parents.
4
5
B. The task force shall electronically submit to the Governor,
5
6
the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the
6
7
House of Representatives, a report on or before November 1, 2027,
7
8
detailing its findings and recommendations.
8
9
C. The task force shall be composed of nine (9) members as
9
10
follows:
10
11
1. The Speaker of the House of Representatives or designee;
11
12
2. The President Pro Tempore of the Senate or designee;
12
13
3. Two designees of the Director of Human Services; and
13
14
4. Five members appointed by the Governor as follows:
14
15
a. two members of the state court system,
15
16
b. one representative of an organization involved in the
16
17
foster care system,
17
18
c. one representative of a nonprofit or faith-based
18
19
organization, and
19
20
d. one person with experience advocating for biological
20
21
families.
21
22
D. The Governor shall select, from the appointed members, a
22
23
chair of the task force who shall have the authority to create
23
24
committees and name committee chairs to facilitate the work of the
24
Req. No. 2882 Page 2

1
task force and shall have the authority to appoint task force
1
2
members and non-members to serve on committees.
2
3
E. The task force shall meet as often as deemed necessary by
3
4
the chair allowing for timely completion of its work. A majority of
4
5
the members shall constitute a quorum for the purpose of conducting
5
6
the business of the task force.
6
7
F. Members, including those appointed to committees who are not
7
8
members of the task force, shall serve without compensation.
8
9
G. The Department of Human Services shall provide staff and
9
10
administrative support for the task force. All officers, agencies,
10
11
and employees of the state shall cooperate with the task force,
11
12
including providing any information, data, records, and reports as
12
13
may be requested.
13
14
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
